    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The slicer beetle sports specialized mouthparts that scissor apart flesh for easier consumption. Each side of its horizontally closing mandibles fits into the other with barely a hair\u2019s breadth to spare. These creatures prefer to dwell in compact caves or warrens. A typical slicer beetle measures 10 feet long and weighs 800 pounds."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This squat but nevertheless large beetle moves with a swift scuttling motion. Its mandibles appear to be remarkably sharp. </i>",
